Based on my research, here are the breaking changes when upgrading to `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` 10.0 (which uses `Microsoft.OpenApi` v2.x with OpenAPI 3.1 support):

## Breaking Changes & Fixes

### 1. `OpenApiString` / `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` removed

The entire `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` namespace (including `OpenApiString`, `OpenApiInteger`, etc.) is gone. `Schema.Example` now takes a `JsonNode`.

```csharp
// ❌ Old
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// ✅ New
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

### 2. `OpenApiSecurityScheme` as dictionary key

Use the new `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference` type for references in security requirements:

```csharp
// ❌ Old
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
{
    Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
};
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
};

// ✅ New
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new()
    {
        [new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2")] = scopes
    }
};
```

### 3. `Schema.Nullable` removed

OpenAPI 3.1 uses JSON Schema's type array for nullability instead of a separate `nullable` keyword. The `Nullable` property no longer exists on `OpenApiSchema`.

```csharp
// ❌ Old
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// ✅ New — remove "null" from the Type flags
property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

(`JsonSchemaType` is a flags enum in the new library; the framework sets `JsonSchemaType.Null` on optional/nullable properties.)

### 4. `Responses.TryAdd` — unchanged

This still works as-is. No changes needed for `OpenApiResponse`.

---

### Complete fixed code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new()
        {
            [new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2")] = scopes
        }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

**Summary of namespace changes:**
- Remove: `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;`
- Add: `using System.Text.Json.Nodes;`
- Keep: `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;`
